Divisibility by 2 depends only on the last bit (LSB), which is read last (MSB-first, so bit 0 is last). The output depends on the final bit read.

I'll track the last bit seen. State "S" is start, "E" means last bit was 0 (even), "O" means last bit was 1 (odd).

