Divisibility by 8 means the last 3 bits are 000. Reading MSB first, I only need to track the last 3 bits, but actually I need to track state as remainder mod 8.

Reading MSB first, remainder mod 8: new_r = (2*r + bit) mod 8. After all 12 bits, x mod 8 = final remainder. Accept if remainder is 0.

