x mod 8 depends only on the last 3 bits. Reading MSB first, I track the value mod 8 of the bits seen so far. Since only the last 3 bits matter, tracking remainder mod 8 works: appending bit b gives (2*state + b) mod 8.

x ≡ 1 mod 8 means the final state is 1.

